🧾 Expert Override JSON – Field Explanation
📌 Structure
JSON
{
  "FLOW_ID": {
    "target_producer_qm": "...",
    "target_consumer_qm": "...",
    "manual_review": false,
    "exclude_from_target": false,
    "reason": "..."
  }
}
🔑 Top-Level Key
FLOW_ID
Plain text
Format: <producer_app>-><consumer_app>
Example
Plain text
8A->OK
Meaning
Represents one producer → consumer flow
Must match exactly what you see in:
explanation_report.csv
data_quality_issues_report.csv
🧠 Fields Inside Each Flow
1. target_producer_qm
JSON
"target_producer_qm": "QM_8A"
Meaning
The final Queue Manager assigned to the producer application
Must follow canonical rule:
Plain text
QM_<PRODUCER_APP>
Why it matters
Enforces one QM per application
Overrides incorrect or ambiguous AS-IS mapping
2. target_consumer_qm
JSON
"target_consumer_qm": "QM_OK"
Meaning
The final Queue Manager assigned to the consumer application
Must follow:
Plain text
QM_<CONSUMER_APP>
Why it matters
Ensures consumer reads from its own local QM
Removes dependency on legacy routing QMs (like WQ26)
3. manual_review
JSON
"manual_review": false
Meaning
Indicates whether the flow still needs human validation
Values
Value
Meaning
true
Still needs review
false
Approved by expert
Important
If set to false, flow becomes:
Plain text
final_status = approved
4. exclude_from_target
JSON
"exclude_from_target": false
Meaning
Controls whether the flow should be included in the target topology
Values
Value
Meaning
false
Include in target
true
Exclude completely
Use cases
true → invalid / duplicate / irrelevant flow
false → valid business flow
5. reason
JSON
"reason": "QM-level linkage confirmed from full dataset"
Meaning
Human-readable explanation of the decision
Why it matters
Improves explainability
Helps judges understand:
why override was needed
what logic was applied
🎯 Example Explained
JSON
{
  "8A->OK": {
    "target_producer_qm": "QM_8A",
    "target_consumer_qm": "QM_OK",
    "manual_review": false,
    "exclude_from_target": false,
    "reason": "QM-level linkage confirmed from full dataset; canonical ownership applied."
  }
}
